description:
On Coltrane's Untitled 11383 from the Both Directions At Once album, McCoy Tyner takes an epic solo that employs a technique I like to call "Anticipatory Pentatonics." Dive deep into my transcription and learn what makes McCoy Tyner one of the greatest pianists that has ever lived.

Recorded using:
Earthworks SV33
Earthworks PM40
5'3 Hallet Davis Baby Grand

If you'd like to donate to my channel, please do so here: https://paypal.me/aimn
